<i>Buarremon virenticeps</i>
The <b>Green-striped Brush Finch</b> (<i>Arremon virenticeps</i>) is a species of <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bird" title="Bird">bird</a> in the <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Emberizidae" title="Emberizidae">Emberizidae</a> family. It is <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Endemism" title="Endemism">endemic</a> to <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mexico" title="Mexico">Mexico</a>. Its natural <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Habitat" title="Habitat">habitat</a> is subtropical or tropical moist <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Montane_forest" title="Montane forest" class="mw-redirect">montane forests</a>. Until recently, it was placed in the <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Genus" title="Genus">genus</a> <i><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Buarremon" title="Buarremon">Buarremon</a></i>.<sup id="cite_ref-2" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-2"><span>[</span>2<span>]</span></a></sup>
<br />
